<section class="front-section shaded">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="getting-invovled">Getting involved</h2>

    <div class="col-wide">
      <p>The development is happening in the <a href="https://github.com/neovim/neovim">GitHub repository</a>. We're discussing the project in IRC (the <strong>#neovim</strong> channel on <strong>irc.freenode.net</strong>) and in the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/neovim">Neovim Google Group</a>, so join us there if you'd like to get involved in the development process.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-narrow">
      <p><a href="https://github.com/neovim/neovim" class="btn full-width">View the GitHub project</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="front-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="col-wide">
      <h2 id="faqs">FAQs</h2>

      <dl class="faqs">
        <dt>Is it ready to download and run now with all the features?</dt>
        <dd>No. Although some features are a work in progress, Neovim isn't at a stable point. Using Neovim should be done with caution as things may change.</dd>

        <dt>When will a beta be available?</dt>
        <dd>When it's ready.</dd>

        <dt>What ways will we be able to install Neovim?</dt>
        <dd>Neovim hopes to be available through common package managers such as Homebrew for OS X, apt-get, pacman, and yum.</dd>

        <dt>Will Neovim improve upon the default configuration that was found in Vim?</dt>
        <dd>This is being <a href="https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/276">discussed</a>, but the community seems to be in favor of it.</dd>

        <dt>Can I donate to Neovim's development?</dt>
        <dd>Yes you can, take a look at the <a href="#donate">Donate section</a> to learn more.</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="col-narrow">
      <h2>Stay informed</h2>

